While in the five years between 2005 and 2010, RPGs from rentals could invest four billion in apartments, in the four years from 2011 to 2014 it is supposed to be 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging at the ceiling opposite the padded seats of the Haví<0xC5><0x99>ov waiting room so far repeats several red highlighted information.
"The rent increase in 2011 by 15% and less affects 31,200 apartments, that's more than 90% of RPG apartments."
"And it will always be at most about 7.50 CZK per square meter and month," appears on the screen.
