Prime Minister Zapatero seems to have understood this, too, and his double statement (reforms promised after a meeting with big businesses last Saturday and yesterday’s announcement of new measures) suggests that despite criticism of Merkel, the way has been opened to the idea that things need to be put in order.
But the red line that Germany has drawn is there, and it does not seem to want to move.
